[[2026-04-14 20:40:08]] {Bash: git commit -m "$(cat <<'EOF'
Improve LLM citation quality with few-shot prompting and context fallback

Small local LLMs (Gemma 4 E4B) produce good analysis but inconsistently
cite VZ_REQ IDs inline despite instruction-based prompting. Two fixes:

1. Few-shot citation example in all system prompts showing the exact
   format expected (inline VZ_REQ IDs + 3GPP TS refs per claim)
2. Context-based citation fallback in LLMSynthesizer — when the LLM
   cites fewer than MIN_REQ_CITATIONS=2 req IDs, supplement from the
   retrieved context chunks that were fed to the LLM
3. Enhanced end-of-context reminder listing all available req IDs

Verified: SMS query went from 0 to 10 req ID citations. 383 tests passing.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
EOF
)" }
